No fewer than 11 persons have been killed by suspected Fulani militia in an attack on Kagoro and some other communities in the Kaura Local Government Area of Kaduna State It was learnt that the attackers who stormed Kagoro in the early hours of Sunday had been carrying out attacks almost every day, killing and burning houses. File photo used to illustrate story. “Besides those who have been confirmed killed by the attackers, l cannot give you the number of those injured because people take their injured relatives to hospital for treatment. "About 50 houses were razed by the attackers,” a source told Daily Post, alleging that the attack was carried out by Fulani militia. The present situation is calm as people and vehicles are moving freely. "As usual, security men are moving around the area to ensure sustainable peace and avert any unforeseen attack," the source said. The state Police Public Relations Officer, ASP Mohammed Jalige, promised to contact the Kafanchan Area Commander to get more information.